STCC TCR SCANDINAVIA:
Young driver @hugonerman 🇸🇪 returns to @stcc_official with @kageredracing, driving a Volkwagen Golf TCR.

description:
Bye bye 2020!
Thanks Thanks Friends - Family - Fans - Sponsors.
The 2020 a very hard & dark year for almost everyone. A year that we were slaves and not free, to feel controlled by a bunch of clowns. We have fought almost every day for our jobs, bussiness, see childrens following ridiculous  school class on a screen meanwhile watching the world fall down. I have seen many friends had a very bad time with medical, financial and personal issues ... but we have moved forward, we have done miracles to survive. 
Friends have been friends, family has been family and we have come against all odds to 2021. THank #god 2020 is almost gone, let’s hope and pray to God that 2021 will be a #possitive year to everyone and thanks you #friends & #family for being there! #BigSupport 
For 2021 we are the same humble, honest, sincere, friend of friends, always you are going to be welcome with a hug!

Designs By Guillermo, presents to you a rare creation. Just like racing, it’s takes a team to have success. Furthermore to win a race, set a lap record, or win a Championship a team is everything. The next few years DBG’s team will grow tremendously. 
.
..
The time consumption that was allocated into this detail oriented handcrafted necktie #23 of 26 originals provided an encouraging reminder to, “keep chasing those dreams & find your passion”. The name Jacobs... remember this last name as the story of a slight failure/setback during collegiate studies will be revealed at a later time 😎 
.
..
The #23, “M. Jacobs Black on Black Check w/ Red Silk & Sewn on Porsche Badge.” With the heritage of German quality in my family lineage I felt the necessity to create a one of a kind handcrafted necktie to appreciate @porsche. 
.
.
..
As a designer collaboration is crucial. I plan on making a couple of these Porsche neckties with slight variations and shipping to a couple of Porsche drivers for promotional purposes. I also plan on contacting many other Porsche company employees to boost this product even further. Thanks for all of the support, thanks for the many likes, thanks for the word of mouth. Lastly, I will own one of these vehicles one day and will be sure to share the bittersweet feeling I use to have as a child for this brand but have grown to love the brand. Chao For Now 🏎💨🇩🇪
.
..

Designs By Guillermo, presents to you a rare creation. The time consuming, detail oriented, meticulous, stylish, multi-fabric handcrafted necktie #23 of 26 originals. The name Jacobs... remember this last name as the story of a slight failure/setback during collegiate studies will be revealed at a later time 😎 
.
..
The #23, “M. Jacobs Black on Black Check w/ Red Silk & Sewn on Porsche Badge.” With the heritage of German quality in my family lineage I felt the necessity to create a one of a kind handcrafted necktie to appreciate @porsche. 
.
..
The History of Porsche & the manufacturer logo dated back to Stuttgart, Germany 🇩🇪 Located in SW Germany, built atop a horse-breeding Farm. Stuttgart used horses in its city seal, inspiring Porsche to make a black horse the centerpiece of its logo which represents power. Basically Stuttgart means “stud fam.” Everlasting quality is crucial in business longevity. 
.
..
As a designer collaboration is crucial. I plan on making a couple of these Porsche neckties with slight variations and shipping to a couple of Porsche drivers for promotional purposes. I also plan on contacting many other Porsche company employees to boost this product even further. Thanks for all of the support, thanks for the many likes, thanks for the word of mouth. Lastly, I will own one of these vehicles one day and will be sure to share the bittersweet feeling I use to have as a child for this brand but have grown to love the brand.
.

Designs By Guillermo, presents to you a rare creation. The time consuming, detail oriented, meticulous, stylish, multi-fabric handcrafted necktie #23 of 26 originals. The name Jacobs... remember this last name as the story of a slight failure/setback during collegiate studies will be revealed at a later time 😎 
.
..
The #23, “M. Jacobs Black on Black Check w/ Red Silk & Sewn on Porsche Badge.” With the heritage of German quality in my family lineage I felt the necessity to create a one of a kind handcrafted necktie to appreciate @porsche. 
.
..
The manufacturing of necktie demanded many hours with similarities to Porsche car making. This necktie required the utmost strategic pattern making and sewing skills. It also required a total of 4 different panels, 1 badge & several layers of interlining. 
.
..
As a designer collaboration is crucial. I plan on making a couple of these Porsche neckties with slight variations and shipping to a couple of Porsche drivers for promotional purposes. I also plan on contacting many other Porsche company employees to boost this product even further. Thanks for all of the support, thanks for the many likes, thanks for the word of mouth. Lastly, I will own one of these vehicles one day and will be sure to share the bittersweet feeling I use to have as a child for this brand but have grown to love the brand.
.
..

caption: Me going out for qualifying at Monza in my Porsche carrera gt3 911 cup car.
description:
One of the most interesting and challenging qualifying sessions to date!🇮🇹 I had a lot of new things, both driving and car wise, to take into consideration going into qualifying which I knew would be a challenge. However, I improved with each lap and got more and more comfortable with the track. In the end I had a hard time putting a proper lap together but P20 has to be considered a good position given my limited amount of practice this year. Feeling really good ahead of tomorrow!🌪🌪
.

caption: Me in my red Porsche 911 gt3 carrera cup car racing at Monza.
description:
All curbs diet in the practice!🍕 I really enjoyed getting to know the track in yesterday’s practice around Monza. The curbs needed to be fully attacked in order to get a quick lap time which proved to be quite difficult since it was my first time on the track. Especially since being a couple of centimetres of the proper spot unsettled the car and sent the car off line. Going out for qualifying in a little while!👊🏁
.

description:
🚘 Ellerim terli, gözlerimse stresten yaşlı. Piste çıkıyoruz. Kendi klasmanımda 5. sıradayım. Önümde adeta uzay mekiklerini andıran LMP01 ve LMP02 prototip otomobilleri yer almakta. Sıralamanın başında şimdilik güvenlik aracı duruyor. Yavaşça sağa sola doğru ilerleyerek lastiklerimi biraz olsun ısıtmayı beceriyorum. Dikiz aynama bakıyorum ve onlarca pilotun stresli yüzlerini az da olsa içimde hissedebiliyorum. Gridde tüm otomobiller teker teker sıralanıyor. Yarış başladığı an içimdeki kötülüklerin gideceğini umuyorum. 6 kırmızı ışık yanıyor. Ve! Tüm ışıklar sönüyor yarış başlıyor...

🌪3rd to 19th to 5th, in the same 20min race last time around at Fällfors. Since @carreracupscandinavia is racing there today we look back to the 2019 race. 

Race 1: Probably the calmest race of the season. Started 4th and finished 4th.

Race 2: The polar opposite to race 1. I
challenged for 2nd place but a technical problem resulted in a spin on lap 2. Got going again, but was way back in 19th place. The chase was on. Thankfully the safety car was brought out  Worked my way from P18 to P5 in 8 laps whilst driving partly blind since a section of the crucial dashboard wasn’t working.
.

⁣Most difficult race weekend of the season🏁 Since Porsche Carrera Cup was competing at Falkenberg today we look back to the Formula STCC race there in 2017.⠀
⠀
We learnt loads during the practice but I didn’t manage to get a great feeling for the car. We did some changes ahead of the qualifying and improved a bit to grab P4 and P3.⠀
⠀
Starting fourth in the first race I snatched P2 after a couple of great battles. The second race was an interesting one as well with plenty of fights and a safety car in the middle. Made a big launch after the safety car and managed to secure second place again.⠀
⠀
All in all an we were lacking pace but managed great results regardless.⠀
⠀
⠀

Season premiere this weekend! Unfortunately participation in the opening races this season won’t be possible for us.
.
Since many of our partners are affected economically, competing in a full season isn’t a viable alternative. We understand their situation and try to help out wherever possible so everyone gets through the year.
.
In the meantime we tune in and cheer for our competitors at Falkenberg tomorrow.
We can hopefully get back on track further on in the season!

description:
🚘 | Sadelik ve zarafetin birleştiği son nokta: #CarreraS. İnsanlar 2000'li yılların başından itibaren hız kavramını anlamaya başlamıştı. Otomobil markaları ise hız ve gücü fazlasıyla abartıp son derece egzotik ve kullanışsız otomobiller üretmeye başlamışlardı. #MclarenF1 ve #BugattiVeyron araçları insanlar tarafından takdir toplasa da gündelik kullanıma uygun olmadığı için beğenilmiyordu. Porsche ise insanların yardımına Carrera'yla koştu. Hem hız, hem de konfor isteyen kişilere biçilmiş kaftan olan Porsche 911 Carrera serisi 1963 yılından beri üretilmektedir.

⁣Race rewind 2019 🔁 Knutstorp📍 After a total of 2 days in the car we had modest expectations for season opener at Knutstorp. We learnt as much as possible during practice and ended qualifying as P3 and P8. ⠀
⠀
In race 1 we saw an incident immediately on the starting straight, but were able to continue relatively unharmed. After fighting off Villeneuve and keeping up the pace we finished the race in 5th place.⠀
⠀
As we lined up for Race 2 the skies suddenly opened and everyone swapped to wet tires. Struggling with pace initially, due to limited wet experience, I improved throughout the race and eventually brought the car home in 6th position.⠀
⠀
📸@eliasstihl, Micke Fransson, SvenskMotorsportFoto.se⠀
⠀

description: Throwback to @carreracupscandinavia Development camp a few weeks ago🤙🏽 #porsche #carreracupscandinavia #driverdevelopment #pccs2020 @porsche @porsche_norge @carreracupscandinavia @teamnorway 📸 @arminiiius

The Porsche Driver Development Programme’s first event took place up in Åre last weekend. A couple of intense days saw the young group of talented drivers develop their car control on ice, cardio training on skis and coaching from the strong lineup behind the program.
•
“This is a great opportunity for me as a driver, both on and off track as well as in between races. I look forward learning new skills that I can use to become a faster and more professional driver.” said Edvin Hellsten after the weekend. Follow the link in our bio @nova_racing and read the full story.
•
📸 Armin Hadžić
•

Thank you guys for an awesome weekend together with @carreracupscandinavia Driver Development Programme! @porschesweden @porschecenterjonkoping #porsche #porschecarreracup #driverdevelopment #pccs2020 #supercup #mobil1supercup @tornfrakt |📸 @arminiiius

Just nu pågår kickoff av Driver Development Programme 2020 i Åre! Porsche Motorsport och ett team av professionella instruktörer möter årets förare under tre intensiva träningsdagar.

@carreracupscandinavia förarutvecklingsprogram inleds med e-learning, föreläsningar och längdskidåkning. De mest uppskattade passen på träningsschemat är självklart avancerad bilkörning på Helgesjöns finslipade is!

Årets förare i Driver Development Programme är Edvin Hellsten, Emil Heyerdahl, Hampus Ericsson, Hugo Andersson, Hugo Nerman, Pontus Fredricsson.

Årets DDP-instruktörer. Körteknik: Björn Wirdheim. Personlig träning: Thomas Fogdö. Medieträning: Fredrik Huldt. Teknik och dataanalys: Marcus Fasth. Fysisk träning och diet: TBC.

#porsche #carreracupscandinavia #driverdevelopment #pccs2020

Roar Lindland dubbelt på pallen på Gelleråsen Arena! Pole position blev en 2:a plats i race 1 - och en 2:a startposition blev en 3:e plats i race 2 för norrmannen. 
Hugo Nerman gjorde även han en bra helg med inspirerad körning som resulterade i en 6:e och en 4:e plats. 
Vi ser fram att göra emot att fortsätta den positiva trenden i de två återstående tävlingarna på Rudskogen 13-14 september och finalen på Mantorp Park 4-5 oktober. 
Racen från Gelleråsen Arena finns att återse på Viaplay tom tisdag. Därefter kommer de att kunna ses på Porsche Carrera Cup Scandinavias YouTube kanal.

description: Last #weekend @carreracupscandinavia and the GT4 Scandinavia with the Porsche Endurance Trophy came together at the Drivecenter Arena in Fällfors, #Sweden 🇸🇪. The Midnattssolsloppet ("Midnight sun race") took place at 8:50 p.m. during full sunlight and thus was truly a race to remember. Did you know? description:
Sjunde titeln för mesta STCC-mästarna Kristoffersson Motorsport

Inget annat team har tagit så många STCC-titlar som Kristoffersson Motorsport, Volkswagen Dealer Team Bauhaus. Sedan deras första säsong 1998 har de tagit sju titlar där Johan Kristoffersson, son till teamets grundare Tommy Kristoffersson, säkrade sin andra titel under 2018-finalen på Mantorp Park.

Andra STCC-titeln efter mästerlig uppvisning av Kristoffersson! Stort grattis @kristofferssonjohan och @vwdealerteam!! 🥇🏆🍾
Läs mer om den dramatiska finalen på Mantorp Park via länk i bio.

STCC rounds 5 & 6 at Falkenberg Motorbana: Robert Dahlgren scores his first win of the year in race 1 ahead of Johan Kristoffersson and Daniel Haglöf. In race 2 Mattias Andersson takes his first STCC win since 2016 with Fredrik Ekblom on P2 and Tobias Brink on P3
Top 3 Race 1:
1 Robert Dahlgren - PWR Racing - Seat Dealer Team Cupra TCR
2 Johan Kristoffersson - VW Dealer Team Bauhaus VW Golf GTI TCR
3 Daniel Haglöf - PWR Racing - Seat Dealer Team Cupra TCR

Top 3 Race 2:
1 Mattias Andersson - Honda Racing Sweden Honda Civic TCR
2 Fredrik Ekblom - WestCoast Racing VW Golf GTI TCR
3 Tobias Brink - Brink Motorsport Audi RS3 LMS
(pics from @stccofficial website)

caption: Photo by Joakim Jardenberg in Ring Knutstorp with @hugonerman.
description:
"I don't know better, I only know different" Mentoring is great, reversed mentoring is better. So it's truly my privilege to be the  mentor/mentee of Hugo Nerman, a young racecar driver from my hometown Helsingborg. I learn so much from him. 
Today it's his premiere in #STCC, and after a great qualification yesterday I really look forward to the two races this afternoon. Another step for Hugo, towards becoming world champion in F1. I have no doubt that's where he'll end up. 
#anotherthingtoday #hugonerman #tcr

caption: Photo by STCC in Ring Knutstorp with @jessbackman, @oliversoderstrom_nr9, @philipmorin, @nicklas.oscarsson, @andreasbckman, and @hugonerman.
description:
|| JTCC ||
JTCC har körts i olika former genom åren, exempelvis Volvo S60 Challenge och Renault Clio Cup. Detta är första gången som JTCC körs inom huvudklassen STCC där juniorerna kör med samma biltyp som övriga förare. – Genom att köra i huvudklassen med samma bilar som alla andra i STCC och dessutom världscupen WTCR får juniorerna den bästa tänkbara utbildningen inför framtiden för att såväl hitta en styrning hos toppteamen i STCC som att hitta internationella körningar, säger Hans Bååth styrelseordförande i STCC.

Tidigare JTCC-mästare inkluderar toppförare som Jens Edman, Daniel Haglöf, Linus Ohlsson och Jocke Mangs.
#JTCC #STCC #TCR #championship #racing #racedriver
